'''The Shore''' is a cross-platform [[Special:MyLanguage/Worlds|world]] created by Blue Cat and was published in 2019. It is set in a minimalistic environment by the sea with two planets and a sun seen faintly behind fog. There is also a [https://vrchat.com/home/launch?worldId=wrld_eb488a9b-7fdd-4671-9726-16c4f19552d3 Night Version] of this world, that was published separately in 2020.

== Design ==
[[File:The Shore Day.jpg|thumb|View towards the sea of the original version of The Shore]]
The spawn is an enclosed bay surrounded by minimalistic structures. Different areas of the map are easily accessible through doors that have a white border, which teleport there. In the distance two planets and several towers are faintly visible, nearly vanishing behind a layer of fog.
The World retains a consistent orange color pallet across all visuals.

=== Night version ===
[[File:The Shore Night.jpg|thumb|View towards the sea of The Shore Night]]
A year after The Shore was published, The Shore [Night] was published. It is designed exactly the same as the original version but opts for a blue-to-teal color pallet instead. Any rooms indoors are lit up in this version. Additionally, the Music used is modified.

== Music == 
The Music used is made by the creator as well and uses four different stems, whose volumes change depending on the current location. For the night version, these stems have been additionally modified to be more calming.
The tracks used for [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vLsKOm1DjX4 the original] and [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VsBz4PYGrWs the night version] can be found uploaded to the creator's YouTube channel.